  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Agent collaboration begins when the client agent discovers a remote agent by retrieving its agent card, i.e., a standardized JSON file typically hosted at a well-known URL.",
    "This agent card contains essential metadata, including agent's capabilities, skills, endpoint address, and authentication requirements, enabling structured agents discovery across diverse systems.",
    "Then, the client agent initiates a task by sending a request containing a unique task ID via universally unique identifier (UUID).The remote agent handles the task according to its declared capabilities.",
    "For asynchronous tasks, intermediate server-sent events (SSE) are streamed as the task progresses, providing status updates and partial response.",
    "In contrast, synchronous tasks return the final result directly in the response."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}